'''Helen Sahagian''' was (1920 &ndash; March 28, 2013) an author, writer, historian, and a founding member of the National Association for the Armenian Studies and Research (NAASR).<ref name=mazda>{{cite book|last=Hovannisian|first=ed. by Richard G.|title=Armenian Sebastia/Sivas and Lesser Armenia|year=2004|publisher=Mazda Publ.|location=Costa Mesa, Calif.|isbn=1568591527}}</ref>

Helen Sahagian has conducted independent research on several Armenian subjects, with particular attention to the work of the American missionaries in [[Sivas]] and [[Van (Turkey)|Van]]. Her articles have been published in the ''Journal of Armenian Studies'', ''Ararat'', and the ''Armenian Mirror-Spectator'' newspaper.<ref name=mazda /> She has participated in the work of the Sebastasti Compatriotic Union and the Historical Commission of [[Arlington, Massachusetts]].<ref name=mazda />

